body_text.text:
The number of NRCs increased from 12 in 1995 to 15 in 2009. Presently, 19 NRCs have been appointed (Table 1
). Five laboratories are situated at the RKI; the others are located at various universities and research facilities in Germany. Since 1996, 46 CLs have decreased to 40 designated CLs, mainly devoted to providing scientific advice (Table 2
). Currently a total of 59 NRCs and CLs located at universities, federal or state institutes and private laboratories are supported for this function by the RKI.
